Here is a full example of what you might do and write when contributing to the [First Contributions](https://github.com/firstcontributions/first-contributions) project using the command line:

---

### ðŸ§¾ **Step-by-Step Commands & Code**

#### 1. **Fork the repository**

Go to: [https://github.com/firstcontributions/first-contributions](https://github.com/firstcontributions/first-contributions)
Click the **Fork** button on the top right.

---

#### 2. **Clone the forked repository**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/first-contributions.git
cd first-contributions
```

Replace `<your-username>` with your actual GitHub username.

---

#### 3. **Create a new branch**

```bash
git checkout -b add-john-doe
```

---

#### 4. **Edit the `Contributors.md` file**

Open the file in a text editor, e.g.:

```bash
nano Contributors.md
```

Add your name like this (scroll to the end or find a good spot alphabetically):

```md
- John Doe
```

Save and close the file.

---

#### 5. **Stage and commit the change**

```bash
git add Contributors.md
git commit -m "Add John Doe to Contributors list"
```

---

#### 6. **Push your branch to GitHub**

```bash
git push origin add-john-doe
```

---

#### 7. **Create a Pull Request**

Go to your fork on GitHub:
[https://github.com/](https://github.com/)<your-username>/first-contributions

GitHub will prompt you to **Compare & pull request**.

Click the button and fill out the PR form like this:

---

### âœ… **Pull Request Title**

```
Add John Doe to Contributors list
```

---

### ðŸ’¬ **Description**

```markdown
### What
This pull request adds my name, John Doe, to the Contributors list in the Contributors.md file.

### Why
This is my first contribution to an open-source project. I'm following the First Contributions tutorial to learn the GitHub flow.

### How
- Forked the repo
- Cloned it locally
- Created a branch
- Added my name
- Committed the change with a clear message
- Pushed the branch
- Opened this pull request

### Before and After
- Before: My name was not listed in Contributors.md
- After: My name is listed among the contributors

### Label
- Documentation

### Notes
This PR uses accessible, input-agnostic language following Microsoft's accessibility guidelines.
```

---

Let me know if you'd like this rewritten using **your actual name** or a **different file change** instead!
